The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 August is 2,904 (336.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 August, there were 39 new confirmed cases (4.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 August, there were 21 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 86% (18 extra cases).
